Good day all,

I fixed yet another case of sunsetting python nosetests.  In
this instance I could have removed straight away the test
dependency, given that build time tests were disabled anyway,
but I ended up noticing how upstream run their tests in their
file .travis.yml, which luckily had nothing to do with nose.

Bringing back the build time test suite raised an issue of
compatibility with python3.11 which was not caught by running
the autopkgtest: something about open() mode 'U' having no
effect in python3 and obsoleted in python3.11.

So bug #1018636 is fixed and scoary is now ready for python3.11.

Have a nice day,  :)
